item.description:
@usman555 wrote:

link: http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
when you get the program, create a shortcut on dektop.
then to start a new project:
step 1)click file,
step 2)new,
step 3)project,
step 4)click next when something pops up,
step 5)then make a project name anything you like, then press finish

now in the workspace,
put this code

[code]
public class (((Your project’s name goes here!! For example, lets say your project name was bananas, put bananas here))) {
public static void main(String[] args) {

}

}[/code]
Your project name was the name when you were making a new project In step 5.
this is what your workbox should look like:

[code]
public class bananas {
public static void main(String[] args) {

}

}[/code]

Now start writing stuff here:

public class bananas { public static void main(String[] args) { WRITE STUFF HERE!!! } }
